d 'XTPVARCOINT': module to perform Panel VAR Modeling with Cointegration, Structural Breaks, and Cross-Sectional Dependence
d
d   xtpvarcoint implements a comprehensive econometric toolkit for
d vector autoregressive (VAR) modeling in heterogeneous panels.   
d It is a Stata port of the R package pvars and provides:	
d Panel cointegration rank tests based on the Johansen procedure
d (Larsson et al. 2001), the Breitung (2005) two-step		
d estimator, the Saikkonen-Luetkepohl procedure (Arsova and Oersal
d 2018), and the correlation-augmented inverse normal		
d test robust to cross-sectional dependence (Arsova and Oersal
d 2021).	Panel VAR/VECM estimation using the mean-group (MG)
d and pooled mean-group (PMG) estimators with optional Kilian
d (1998)	    bias correction and factor-augmented
d specifications for cross-sectional dependence.	Panel SVAR
d identification via Cholesky decomposition, Blanchard-Quah
d long-run restrictions, proxy/IV variables, distance		
d covariance (DC), and Cramer-von Mises (CVM) independence
d criteria.	   Specification tools for determining the number
d of common factors (Onatski 2010, Ahn and Horenstein 2013, Bai and
d Ng 2002)	      and the optimal lag order based on AIC, HQC,
d SIC, and FPE criteria.	Impulse response functions,
d {bf:forecast error variance decomposition}, and bootstrap
d confidence intervals via the panel		moving-block
d bootstrap.	    Publication-quality plots for IRFs with
d confidence bands, FEVD stacked area charts, and companion matrix
d eigenvalue		stability diagrams.    The data must be
d xtset before calling xtpvarcoint.  Individual-specific lag orders
d are supported by specifying a numlist in    lags(). 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: panel VAR
d KW: panel VECM
d KW: cointegration
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260405
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
